title: Nigerian rescuers work to reach survivors after building collapses
text:
Lagos - Rescue teams worked overnight on Wednesday in Lagos to reach people trapped under the rubble of a three-storey building that collapsed earlier in the day.
An unknown number of residents were in the building on Lagos Island when it collapsed shortly after 09:00, said Okone Macauly, assistant director of the city's Federal Fire Service.
"Initially we rescued four people from the building who were slightly injured," he said.
"The cause of the collapse hasn't been ascertained, but the building was weak."
